question: Ethan places cookies on some trays. Each tray can hold 35 cookies. If he has 184 cookies and 3 trays, how many cookies won't he be able to place on the tray?
answer:
Ethan will be able to place a total of 35*3 = <<35*3=105>>105 cookies.
Therefore, there are 184 - 105 = <<184-105=79>>79 cookies that he won't be able to place on the tray.
#### 79
